        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer692790705" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5599056424286921083"><br/>Positives: All the stories, the writing style in each and the message is different, though they are centered around a common theme. This is difficult and brilliantly done by Meghna. In most stories I couldnt and didnt want to predict what happens next, I was happy to flow with the story.<br/>Negatives: Two of the stories The Gecko on the Wall and Clip and cane are predictable. Though Lemon and Chilli also is but I just loved the way it was presented.<br/><br/>The Verdict: Highly Recommended for short story lov</span>
  <span id="freeText5599056424286921083" style="display:none"><br />Positives: All the stories, the writing style in each and the message is different, though they are centered around a common theme. This is difficult and brilliantly done by Meghna. In most stories I couldnt and didnt want to predict what happens next, I was happy to flow with the story.<br />Negatives: Two of the stories The Gecko on the Wall and Clip and cane are predictable. Though Lemon and Chilli also is but I just loved the way it was presented.<br /><br />The Verdict: Highly Recommended for short story lovers. 4 stars on 5.</span>
